    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "APRIL 1, 1945\nTWA\nPOINTS THE WAY\nThe New Stratoliner Over Kansas City\nCopyright 1945. Transcontinentel 8 Western Air. Inc.",
      "TOLEDO\nOAKLANO\nDenver\nColorado Springs\nTH BE IT WAYNE\nLAS VEGAS YO\nKANSAS CITYA\n•ТОРЕКА\nGRAND CANYON\nALBUQUERQUE\nWINSLOW\nL. EG END\nTWA SYSTEM\nCONNECTING TINES\nSOUTH AMERICA\nFiner and faster-\nthe new Stratoliners\noffer coast-to-coast service\nTWA\nPOINTS THE WAY\nTRANSCONTINENTAL \u0026 WESTERN AIR, INC.\nTWA GENERAL OFFICES\n101 W. 11th St.,\nKansas City o, Mo.\nT. B. WILSON—Ch. of Board\nJACK FRYE—President\nE. LEE TALMAN—Exec. V.-Pres.\nJ. A. COLLINGS—V.-Pres., Transp.\nC. E. FLEMING—V.-Pres.\nJ. C. FRANKLIN —V.-Pres., Eng.\nOTIS F. BRYAN—V.-Pres.\nJACK NICHOLS—V.-Pres\nE. O. COCKE—V.-Pres., Traffic\nJOHN B. THURSTON—Treasurer\nA. M. JENS, JR.—Secretary\nJ. C. GRAVES—Mgr. Agency Dept."
